-- NH Hoteles Seeks to Manage State Hotel Chain, Economista Says
-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 2012-01-17T06:27:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/nh-hoteles-seeks-to-manage-state-hotel-chain-economista-says.html
NH Hoteles SA (NHH)  and closely held
Hoteles Barcelo are interested in contracts to manage  Spain ’s
state-owned hotel chain,  El Economista  reported, citing
unidentified officials at both companies.  While the chain of 93 hotels, which employs almost 4,500
people, won’t be sold, the government may contract out the
management of the properties, the newspaper added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid  at 
